The President delivered a speech at a private residence in New York, discussing various topics including climate change and environmental policies. He emphasized the importance of the United States taking a leading role in addressing climate change and rejoining the Paris Accord as his first act in office. The President thanked the audience for their support and contributions to the fight against climate change, acknowledging their role in raising awareness and investing in solutions. He highlighted the need for bipartisan cooperation and listed several accomplishments, such as passing the Infrastructure Law, increasing investment in clean energy, and promoting electric vehicles. The President expressed optimism about the future and praised the younger generation for their understanding and commitment to environmental issues. He concluded by taking questions from the audience.